# Automation Runtime

Cloud agent containers for this repo are configured via `.cursor/environment.json`.

## Boot sequence

On each run, Cursor executes `.cursor/scripts/agent-bootstrap.sh`, which runs `npm ci` and verifies tooling.

## Available tools

- **Node / npm** — project dependencies and `npm test`
- **python** and **python3** — `python-is-python3` in the cloud Dockerfile
- **gh** — read-only GitHub issue/PR queries when authenticated
- **open_git_pr** MCP — only writable GitHub path in automations

## Do not assume

- `gh issue comment` / `gh issue edit` (write-disabled in automations)
- Bare `python` without checking PATH — prefer `python3`, `node`, `npm`, or webhook payload JSON

## Handoff patterns

| Agent type | Apply results via |
|------------|-------------------|
| DISPATCH | `.openbook/dispatch/issue-<n>.yaml` + `open_git_pr` → `router-apply-dispatch-pr.yml` |
| RESEARCH | `.openbook/research/issue-<n>.yaml` + PR → `router-apply-research-pr.yml` |
| Execution agents | `.openbook/execution/issue-<n>.yaml` + PR → `router-apply-execution-pr.yml` |
| REVIEW | PR comment with `<!-- openbook-author:review -->` → `router-apply-review.yml` |

## Pipeline concurrency

Only **one cloud agent** runs at a time by default (override via repo variable `OPENBOOK_MAX_CONCURRENT_AGENTS`; set to **8** on Pro).

- `agent-webhook.yml` queues dispatches and skips when `agent-running` is present
- Apply workflows clear `agent-running` when a handoff completes
- Stale locks (>6h) are cleared hourly by `agent-running-cleanup.yml`

If a label is skipped while busy, re-add it after the current agent finishes.

Cursor plan limits still apply separately (e.g. Pro allows multiple concurrent cloud agents account-wide).

## Issue context

Prefer parsing the webhook payload first. Fallback read-only:

```bash
gh issue view <number> --json number,title,body,labels,comments
```
